This paper proposes a novel neural network model for representing logical relations, which falls under the categories of neural networks and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design of the neural network model, which involves defining new neurons and links, and introducing inhibitory links. This aspect of the paper could be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed model, which could include expanding the application areas of artificial neural networks. This aspect of the paper could be relevant to the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL), which deals with the design and implementation of programming languages and their applications.
